Description: Gabled sandstone stela of Ioannes; panel of six lines of Greek text above a cross within a wreath, a second cross and palm branches, implying martyrdom.
Bibliographic references: Hall 1905 / Coptic and Greek Texts of the Christian Period from Ostraka, Stelae, etc. in the British Museum (p.133, Pl.93)
